{% layout "layouts/base.liquid" %}
{% block title %}Button — Cubito UI Docs{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="flow">

  <header class="flow" style="padding-block-end: var(--space-l); border-block-end: var(--border-s) solid var(--color-neutral-200);">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb">
      <ol>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/base/">Base Elements</a></li>
        <li aria-current="page">Button</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
    <h1>Button</h1>
    <p class="text-m color-neutral-600">Interactive button controls for <code>&lt;button&gt;</code>, submit and reset inputs, and the <code>.button</code> utility class — with variants, states, icon support, and an elevate preset.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Basic usage</h2>
      <p>Native <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> elements and <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> elements with the <code>.button</code> class are styled identically. No extra class is needed on a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code>.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div class="cluster">
    <button type="button">Save changes</button>
    <a href="#" class="button">Link button</a>
    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;cluster&quot;&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot;&gt;Save changes&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;Link button&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;Submit&quot;&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Variants</h2>
      <p>Four visual variants are available via <code>data-variant</code>. All inherit their colour from the surrounding context so they adapt automatically inside coloured surfaces.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div class="cluster">
    <button type="button">Solid (default)</button>
    <button type="button" data-variant="outline">Outline</button>
    <button type="button" data-variant="ghost">Ghost</button>
    <button type="button" data-variant="naked">Naked</button>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;cluster&quot;&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot;&gt;Solid (default)&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; data-variant=&quot;outline&quot;&gt;Outline&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; data-variant=&quot;ghost&quot;&gt;Ghost&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; data-variant=&quot;naked&quot;&gt;Naked&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>

      <table class="">
        <thead><tr><th>Value</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>—</code> (default)</td><td>Solid fill. Background and border colour are set by <code>--button-background</code> and <code>--button-border-color</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data-variant="outline"</code></td><td>Transparent fill with a visible border. Colour inherits from the parent context.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data-variant="ghost"</code></td><td>No border, subtle fill on hover only. Good for toolbar actions.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data-variant="naked"</code></td><td>Zero chrome — renders like a link. Inherits surrounding typography (size, weight, transform).</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Sizes</h2>
      <p>There is no built-in size attribute. Override <code>--button-font-size</code> and <code>--button-padding</code> inline or at a component scope to produce smaller or larger buttons.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div class="cluster" style="align-items: center">
    <button type="button" style="--button-font-size: 0.75em; --button-padding: 0.25rem 0.625rem">Small</button>
    <button type="button">Default</button>
    <button type="button" style="--button-font-size: 2em; --button-padding: var(--space-s) var(--space-m)">Large</button>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;cluster&quot; style=&quot;align-items: center&quot;&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; style=&quot;--button-font-size: 0.75em; --button-padding: 0.25rem 0.625rem&quot;&gt;Small&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot;&gt;Default&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; style=&quot;--button-font-size: 1em; --button-padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem&quot;&gt;Large&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">With icon</h2>
      <p>Drop an inline SVG directly inside the button. The icon is sized to <code>--button-icon-size</code> (default <code>1.2cap</code>) and never grows or shrinks. For icon-only buttons, provide an <code>aria-label</code> on the button itself.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div class="cluster">
    <button type="button">
      Next
      <svg aria-hidden="true" width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M8 1l7 7-7 7M15 8H1"/></svg>
    </button>
    <button type="button" data-variant="outline">
      <svg aria-hidden="true" width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M8 1l7 7-7 7M15 8H1"/></svg>
      Back
    </button>
    <button type="button" data-variant="ghost" aria-label="Go to next page">
      <svg aria-hidden="true" width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M8 1l7 7-7 7M15 8H1"/></svg>
    </button>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;cluster&quot;&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot;&gt;
      Next
      &lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; width=&quot;1em&quot; height=&quot;1em&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M8 1l7 7-7 7M15 8H1&quot;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; data-variant=&quot;outline&quot;&gt;
      &lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; width=&quot;1em&quot; height=&quot;1em&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M8 1l7 7-7 7M15 8H1&quot;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
      Back
    &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; data-variant=&quot;ghost&quot; aria-label=&quot;Go to next page&quot;&gt;
      &lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; width=&quot;1em&quot; height=&quot;1em&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M8 1l7 7-7 7M15 8H1&quot;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>
      <div class="callout wide" data-variant="brand" role="note"><p>For icon-only buttons, always provide an accessible label via <code>aria-label</code> or a visually hidden <code>&lt;span class="sr-only"&gt;</code>. The SVG should carry <code>aria-hidden="true"</code>.</p></div>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">States</h2>
      <p>Buttons respond to several semantic states. Use native HTML attributes wherever possible — the CSS wires them up automatically.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div class="cluster">
    <button type="button" disabled>Disabled</button>
    <button type="button" data-busy="true">Saving…</button>
    <button type="button" aria-pressed="true">Bookmarked</button>
    <button type="button" aria-expanded="true">Menu open</button>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;cluster&quot;&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; disabled&gt;Disabled&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; data-busy=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Saving…&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; aria-pressed=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Bookmarked&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; aria-expanded=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Menu open&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>

      <table class="">
        <thead><tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>disabled</code></td><td>Muted appearance, pointer events removed. Use <code>aria-disabled="true"</code> on <code>.button</code> anchors.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data-busy="true"</code></td><td>Inline spinner appended via <code>::after</code>. Prevents interaction during async operations.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>aria-pressed="true"</code></td><td>Toggled-on state: filled background, no lift transform. Reflects a persistent toggle (e.g. bookmark, like).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>aria-expanded="true"</code></td><td>Same visual treatment as <code>aria-pressed</code>. Use for disclosure triggers (dropdowns, accordions).</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Elevate preset</h2>
      <p>The <code>data-preset="elevate"</code> attribute adds a hard-offset box shadow that shifts upward on hover and collapses on press. It is orthogonal to variants — compose both together freely.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div class="cluster">
    <button type="button" data-preset="elevate">Elevate</button>
    <button type="button" data-variant="outline" data-preset="elevate">Outline + elevate</button>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;cluster&quot;&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; data-preset=&quot;elevate&quot;&gt;Elevate&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; data-variant=&quot;outline&quot; data-preset=&quot;elevate&quot;&gt;Outline + elevate&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">As link</h2>
      <p>Any <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element with <code>class="button"</code> renders identically to a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code>. Use this for navigation targets. To disable a link-button, use <code>aria-disabled="true"</code> instead of the <code>disabled</code> attribute.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div class="cluster">
    <a href="#" class="button">Go to dashboard</a>
    <a href="#" class="button" data-variant="outline">View details</a>
    <a href="#" class="button" aria-disabled="true">Unavailable</a>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;cluster&quot;&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;Go to dashboard&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; class=&quot;button&quot; data-variant=&quot;outline&quot;&gt;View details&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; class=&quot;button&quot; aria-disabled=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Unavailable&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Tokens</h2>
      <p>All button tokens are defined in <code>@layer tokens</code> on <code>:root</code> and follow the convention <code>[scope]-[variant]-[property]-[optional state]</code>. Override them in <code>@layer theme</code> on <code>:root</code>, or use the internal <code>--button-[property]</code> shorthand for local, per-element overrides.</p>

      <h3 class="heading-m">Default variant — base</h3>
      <table class="">
        <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-background</code></td><td><code>var(--color-neutral-400)</code></td><td>Fill colour.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-border-color</code></td><td><code>var(--color-neutral-600)</code></td><td>Border colour.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-border-width</code></td><td><code>var(--border-m)</code></td><td>Border thickness.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-border-style</code></td><td><code>solid</code></td><td>Border style.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-color</code></td><td><code>var(--color-white)</code></td><td>Label text colour.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-font-size</code></td><td><code>0.875em</code></td><td>Label font size.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-font-weight</code></td><td><code>var(--font-weight-bold)</code></td><td>Label font weight.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-padding</code></td><td><code>var(--space-xs) var(--space-s)</code></td><td>Inner spacing.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-radius</code></td><td><code>var(--border-radius-m)</code></td><td>Corner radius.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-gap</code></td><td><code>var(--space-xs)</code></td><td>Gap between label and icon.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-icon-size</code></td><td><code>1.2cap</code></td><td>Icon block/inline size.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-text-transform</code></td><td><code>uppercase</code></td><td>Label text transform.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-tracking</code></td><td><code>0.05em</code></td><td>Letter spacing.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-raise</code></td><td><code>var(--space-tiny)</code></td><td>translateY distance on hover.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-transition</code></td><td>multi-property</td><td>Transition shorthand for all animated properties.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3 class="heading-m">Default variant — states</h3>
      <table class="">
        <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-background-hover</code></td><td><code>var(--button-default-background)</code></td><td>Fill on hover/focus.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-border-color-hover</code></td><td><code>var(--button-default-border-color)</code></td><td>Border colour on hover/focus.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-color-hover</code></td><td><code>var(--button-default-color)</code></td><td>Text colour on hover/focus.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-opacity-hover</code></td><td><code>0.65</code></td><td>Opacity on hover (not applied by default; available for custom use).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-background-active</code></td><td><code>var(--button-default-background)</code></td><td>Fill while pressed.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-border-color-active</code></td><td><code>var(--button-default-border-color)</code></td><td>Border colour while pressed.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-color-active</code></td><td><code>var(--button-default-color)</code></td><td>Text colour while pressed.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-opacity-busy</code></td><td><code>0.85</code></td><td>Opacity when loading.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-background-toggled</code></td><td><code>var(--color-neutral-500)</code></td><td>Fill for pressed/expanded state.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-border-color-toggled</code></td><td><code>var(--button-default-border-color)</code></td><td>Border colour for toggled state.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-color-toggled</code></td><td><code>var(--button-default-color)</code></td><td>Text colour for toggled state.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-background-disabled</code></td><td><code>var(--color-neutral-200)</code></td><td>Fill when disabled.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-border-color-disabled</code></td><td><code>var(--color-neutral-400)</code></td><td>Border colour when disabled.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-color-disabled</code></td><td><code>var(--color-neutral-500)</code></td><td>Text colour when disabled.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-default-opacity-disabled</code></td><td><code>0.6</code></td><td>Opacity when disabled.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3 class="heading-m">Outline variant</h3>
      <table class="">
        <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--button-outline-background-hover</code></td><td><code>color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 10%, transparent)</code></td><td>Hover fill for outline variant.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-outline-border-color-hover</code></td><td><code>currentColor</code></td><td>Border colour on hover (fallback).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-outline-border-color-active</code></td><td><code>currentColor</code></td><td>Border colour while pressed (fallback).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-outline-color-hover</code></td><td><code>currentColor</code></td><td>Text colour on hover (fallback).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-outline-color-active</code></td><td><code>currentColor</code></td><td>Text colour while pressed (fallback).</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3 class="heading-m">Ghost variant</h3>
      <table class="">
        <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--button-ghost-background-hover</code></td><td><code>color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 10%, transparent)</code></td><td>Hover fill for ghost variant.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3 class="heading-m">Elevate preset</h3>
      <table class="">
        <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--button-elevate-offset</code></td><td><code>0.25rem</code></td><td>Shadow offset distance.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-elevate-shadow</code></td><td><code>0 0 0 var(--button-border-color)</code></td><td>Shadow at rest.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-elevate-shadow-hover</code></td><td>offset shadow</td><td>Shadow on hover.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-elevate-shadow-active</code></td><td><code>none</code></td><td>Shadow while pressed.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-elevate-transform-hover</code></td><td>translateY up</td><td>Transform on hover.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--button-elevate-transform-active</code></td><td><code>translate(0, 0)</code></td><td>Transform while pressed.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3 class="heading-m">Local overrides</h3>
      <p>When scoping to a component, use the internal <code>--button-[property]</code> form to override the current value directly without touching the global tokens.</p>
      <pre class="padding-m"><code>.checkout-form button[type="submit"] {
  --button-background:       var(--color-status-ok);
  --button-border-color:     var(--color-status-ok);
  --button-background-hover: oklch(from var(--color-status-ok) calc(l - 0.08) c h);
}</code></pre>

    </div>
  </section>

</article>
{% endblock %}
